---HEADER---
file:                  tooling/validate.py
language:              python
role:                  Validate subcommand orchestration shell. Walks
                       every island under the project root via
                       iter_islands, calls validate_island on each,
                       calls validate_mainland for connections.llmainland,
                       and aggregates findings into a Report. Holds no
                       parsing logic of its own — the actual checks
                       live in _validate_island, _validate_symbols,
                       and _validate_mainland.
layer:                 io
status:                verified
confidence:            high (rationale: rc8 dogfood proved the validator
                       on mix's own 8 islands. Two real bugs caught and
                       fixed in the same RC. After the file-size split
                       this file is the orchestration shell only.)
generation-pass:       false
read-reason:           task-driven
last-verified:         v0.3-2026-05-07
maintained-by:         llm
exports:
  - cmd_validate
  - setup_validate
  - SUBCOMMANDS
imports:
  - argparse
  - pathlib                       :: Path
  - tooling._validate_island      :: validate_island
  - tooling._validate_mainland    :: validate_mainland
  - tooling.common                :: iter_islands
  - tooling.types                 :: Finding, Report
depends-on:
  - llmisland_tooling.py          :: orchestrator iterates SUBCOMMANDS
translation-boundary:  none
dynamic-boundary:      false

---SYMBOLS---

SYMBOL: cmd_validate
kind:           function
pure:           false (drives validate_island and validate_mainland)
total:          true
latency-budget: O(N) where N = islands; typically <5s
effects:
  reads:    filesystem (every island + mainland)
  mutates:  none
  allocs:   aggregated Finding list + counts dict
  throws:   never
  async:    false
  io:       filesystem read
called-by:
  - llmisland_tooling.main :: dispatch on 'validate'
calls:
  - iter_islands, validate_island, validate_mainland
expects:
  - args has .directory, .include_examples, .no_mainland, .json
runtime-dependencies:
  - none
tests:
  unit:       none yet
  regression: rc8 smoke test: all 3 modes (default, --include-examples,
              --json) pass
  security:   none
business-rule: N/A
fragility:    low (rationale: thin shell; behavior lives in delegated
                  modules)
fragility-note: N/A

SYMBOL: setup_validate
kind:           function
pure:           true (mutates parser passed in)
total:          true
latency-budget: <1ms
effects:
  reads:    none
  mutates:  argparse.ArgumentParser
  allocs:   none meaningful
  throws:   never
  async:    false
  io:       none
called-by:
  - llmisland_tooling.build_parser
calls:
  - parser.add_argument
expects:
  - parser supports add_argument
runtime-dependencies:
  - none
tests:
  unit:       none yet
  regression: none yet
  security:   none
business-rule: N/A
fragility:    low
fragility-note: N/A

SYMBOL: SUBCOMMANDS
kind:           constant
pure:           true
total:          true
latency-budget: N/A
effects:
  reads:    none
  mutates:  none
  allocs:   one dict at import time
  throws:   never
  async:    false
  io:       none
called-by:
  - llmisland_tooling.build_parser :: iterates module.SUBCOMMANDS
calls:
  - none
expects:
  - {'validate': (setup_validate, cmd_validate, helptext)}
runtime-dependencies:
  - none
tests:
  unit:       none yet
  regression: none yet
  security:   none
business-rule: N/A
fragility:    low
fragility-note: N/A

---RISKS---

security:                none
regression-sensitivity:
  - this file is intentionally thin; behavior changes belong in the
    delegated modules (_validate_island, _validate_symbols,
    _validate_mainland), not here
platform-sensitivity:    none
config-dependencies:     none

---MEMORY---

ACTIVE-CONSTRAINTS:
  - id: AC-001
    constraint:  validate.py is the orchestration shell. Do not add
                 parsing or validation logic here; it belongs in the
                 _validate_* modules.
    established: 2026-05-07
    evidence:    HD-001

  - id: AC-002
    constraint:  RULE 8 inline rationale format MUST be honored when
                 enum-checking. enum_token in _validate_island.py is
                 the load-bearing helper.
    established: 2026-05-07
    evidence:    rc8 smoke test (HD-002)

  - id: AC-003
    constraint:  MAINLAND_NAME self-reference is exempt from
                 connection-no-island warnings. Spec docs are not
                 islanded.
    established: 2026-05-07
    evidence:    rc8 smoke test (HD-003)

HISTORICAL-DECISIONS:
  - id: HD-001
    decision:  validate.py is an orchestration shell only; the
               format checks live in package-private modules
    reason:    the original validate.py grew to 635 LOC, well past
               the 400-line red line. Splitting into _enums.py,
               _validate_island.py, _validate_symbols.py, and
               _validate_mainland.py brought every file under the
               red line and gave each a coherent topic. validate.py
               is now the thin entry point that wires the pieces.
    date:      2026-05-07
    outcome:   stable; all files now under 400 LOC
    evidence:  inferred-from-design (file-size rule pressure)

  - id: HD-002
    decision:  enum_token strips inline rationale before enum check
    reason:    SPEC RULE 8 (SPEC/02_SYMBOLS.md) defines
               'field: value (rationale: ...)' as first-class for
               subjective fields. Without stripping, the validator
               rejects every spec-conformant island. Smoke test in
               rc8 went from 33 errors to 0 after this fix.
    date:      2026-05-07
    outcome:   stable; helper now lives in _validate_island.py
    evidence:  rc8 smoke test results in VERSION_HISTORY rc8 entry

  - id: HD-003
    decision:  MAINLAND_NAME self-reference is exempt from
               connection-no-island warnings
    reason:    the mainland is not islanded (notes.md item 8). When
               a tooling file declares a CONNECTION back to
               connections.llmainland (legitimate — rules.py and
               validate.py both read it), the validator should not
               warn that the mainland has no island.
    date:      2026-05-07
    outcome:   stable; tooling mainland's two cycles validate cleanly
    evidence:  rc8 smoke test results

  - id: HD-004
    decision:  format-only validation, not semantic
    reason:    a tool can detect missing fields, bad enums, and
               structural rules. It cannot detect whether a
               rationale is honest or whether security review
               actually happened. Adding semantic checks would
               create false confidence — the tool would say 'ok'
               when the human review was the actual gate. Limiting
               scope keeps the contract honest.
    date:      2026-05-07
    outcome:   stable; matches codex's validator scope
    evidence:  inferred-from-design

SUPERSEDED:
  - none yet
